				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually there was an idea in another thread (not mine) that sounds like it could work without needing to change how things are stored, it does require some special code but that should be easy to fix.
<br />

<br />
Basically, the idea was that the pet would become a no rent item which's properties are coded to show what buffs/etc was on the warder. I think the idea was so you could suspend more than one warder originally but it could help with this too. Each server trigger some code when you zone out, as well as when you zone in (that was how the buff icon worked before, it checked on zonein for the buff and if present gave you the mini-warder).
<br />

<br />
The problem would be to code in the buffs and effects on the warder in a reasonable manner, I dont know if they have any limits on the length of the name of items though, they could possibly set the name to a code of buff numbers (each buff has a spell number) and the duration left as well. Current hps would be possible to see as the +hp on the item, and the level of the warder by the required level. They could even use fields to code in if its shrunk/etc. The zone out code could check if you have SM3 and if you do and have the warder suspended (they could even allow it to work even if its not suspended for beastlords to simulate our lost ability, Im sorta used to not having it now though) and if you do it creates the no rent item and puts that on your cursor (or drops it into inventory). Then when you zone in to the new zone it looks for the item and then recreates the warder from the data it can parse from the no rent item.
<br />

<br />
Not sure if they can get enough space on the item to store all buffs/etc but I do hope that they at least consider it and do some calculations.<br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=360803&resize=true" target="_blank" OnClick="javascript:window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=360803','','width=800,height=600'); return false"><img src="http://home.swipnet.se/Nulli-Secundis/pics/DahkarET.jpg" border="0" alt="Click here to inspect"></a></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
