				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem with the no rent object idea
<br />

<br />
Objects in EQ are copies of a master object, with the only variable existing being the number of charges.
<br />

<br />
So they would even need to code a huge pile of objects to covere every possible combination you might want, or come up with a different way of coding new objects to generate em on the fly, or totally redo objects in general.
<br />

<br />
Or, create a new chunk of space for each character record that stores the pet information.
<br />

<br />
How ever it happens, it would take code cutting.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
