<br />
Thing is, they added the song box so tacking on a buff box for the pet shouldn't be a major thing. It's been proven they can do it if they want to, it's just making them want to do it.
<br />

<br />
As for saving the pet, SM2 already (at least supposedly) stores the pet and all equipment intact, Making SM3 save buffs is what, adding a 3-digit code to represent each of the 15 buff slots (since they are, or at least seem to be, immune to the bard songs you can ignore those 6 buff slots), and a 3-digit code to represent the % left of the spell (for example something like Dexterity is spell 112, you suspend your pet with Dexterity after it's been on the pet for a while, and it would have 112 030 (30% of the total time left) the extra digit on the % would be for the "extended duration buffs") so you could have 112 130 for Dexterity with 130% if it's normal time left. I can't imagine that this would be too horribly difficult considering what they are already storing as far as information.<br />_________________<br />Aliveer Tishar
